CWEs: CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')
description: The function unique_name_559 is vulnerable to Cross-site Scripting (XSS) attacks. The function takes a stringId and subs as parameters and uses them to set the content of an element without properly sanitizing the input. An attacker could potentially inject malicious scripts through these parameters, which would then be executed when the content is rendered on the webpage.
